%N A004135 Additive bases: a(n) is the least integer k such that in the cyclic group Z_k there is a subset of n elements all pairs (of distinct elements) of which add up to a different sum (in Z_k).
%C A004135 From _Fausto A. C. Cariboni_, Oct 08 2017: (Start)
%C A004135 Lexicographically first basis that yields a(n) for n=16:
%C A004135 a(16) = 252 from {0,1,2,4,32,47,54,65,94,120,128,145,169,196,217,240}
%C A004135 (End)
%C A004135 From _Fausto A. C. Cariboni_, Mar 12 2018: (Start)
%C A004135 Lexicographically first basis that yields a(n) for n=17:
%C A004135 a(17) = 255 from {0,1,2,4,8,16,27,32,54,64,99,108,128,141,177,198,216}
%C A004135 (End)
